        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Bleeding disorder due to CalDAG-GEFI deficiency is a rare hematologic disease due to defective platelet function and characterized by mucocutaneous bleeding starting in infancy (around 18 months of age) presenting with prolonged and severe epistaxis hematomas and bleeding after tooth extraction. Massive menorrhagia and chronic anemia have also been reported."
        },
